caption: I visit this place regularly.  Great food.  Good prices.  Friendly service.  Fried Saimin is the BEST! HIGHLY RECOMMENDED.
Food was excellent.  Very tasty.  We ordered mabo tofu dishes with sides of pork katsu and gyoza.  Yummy.  Going back again soon!

It's great to be able to dine in again! I'm so glad they're able to survive the pandemic; I would be sad if they closed for good, like a lotta mom n pop shops (pls support ur mom n pop shops!) Food, as usual, is goooood! I like their combos. Service is fast and the staff is nice. Thank you
The shoyu udon broth is absolutely packed with flavor. Its a must get every time I go there. Also, their curry is thick and amazing.
Hoping this iconic restaurant stays open. It's places like Sanoyas that make Hawaii memorable. 150 gyoza next time ouuuaaaa faborny

Would I go back:  HECK YEAH!  Food:  Mini set - 4/5 - How can you say no to carbs!!!!  A mini ramen and a mini beef curry...it’s the best of both worlds.  Just enough of each to make my tummy satisfied.  I usually crave this when I come to Oahu.  Service: 3/5 - Standard service.  Ambiance: 3/5 - It kind of reminds me of a cafeteria style place.  Sometimes the tables aren’t bussed cause it seems like there are only a couple people on staff.  It’s a casual setting.
Best late night food you can get. Thank you to the only Mexican girl I ever dated for introducing this place to me

Some of the best gyozas in town!! There menu has so many great choices that everyone will find something to their liking! So many of them are tasty comfort food dishes! Great easy going, no frills dining atmosphere , definitely an old-school eatery vibe! Absolutely should be on your list of go to places, especially if your looking for a late night bowl of ramen or even an entire meal!
I LOVE ramen, this place has good ramen

Food has always been good and this is definitely a place for cheap eats! However it does get busy and sometimes you have to wait, as it's only the lady, the same lady since forever, who is waiting on tables. There have been other employees but when I go it's always just her. So be courteous bc she's does her best!  Since they remodeled years ago, there isn't much character to the place. It's too bright,  people's conversations bounce off the walls, the restroom is in clear view of almost everybody dining 😫😫 and there's no music playing. It needs a little dressing up.  I still come here though regardless because the food is good, it's quick and it's open late!
